"Our first project was about Maya prophecy, and in a way we discredited it," says Julie saile, a last-year student at Temple, 21-year-old from West Chester.
The Mayans never predicted the end of the world, it's just a key date on the calendar," said Restall.
But I agree that there is anxiety associated with apocalypse in Western culture, dating back to centuries, which makes people react to changes in their environment by predicting the end of the world.
The Internet has led to a rise in these speculations.
"In other parts of the world, people don't think about it," he says.
Most of this is English speaking.
